main event: On 19 October 1956, a high school student took a time exposure photograph of the moon in Bostonia, California, which accidentally captured what appears to be a UFO.
interesting points: The student reported the sighting to the FBI after discovering the object in her developed photographs., The object resembles a chandelier or a light fixture., Experts analyzed the photographs and suggested the object might be a result of double exposure., There were significant discrepancies in the moon's trail in the photograph, hinting at possible camera movement., The Air Force concluded that the photographed object was likely a hoax, although they did not accuse the student of any wrongdoing.
sighted object: UFO resembling a chandelier or light fixture
witness description: The witness was a 17-year-old high school student taking a photography class.
